ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 19 Jul 2019
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2019; 32(30) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=31143


Sheep pox and goat pox, Kazakhstan
----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 19 Jul 2019 from Dr. Tursyn Kabduldanov, Deputy Chairman, Committee for Veterinary Control and Supervision, Ministry of Agriculture, Nur-Sultan, Kazakhstan

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 15 Jun 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 25 Jun 2019
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Capripoxvirus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Suyunduk, Kurmangazy, Atyrauskaya [Atyrau]
Date of start of the outbreak: 15 Jun 2019
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep / 13 486 / 260 / 260 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 1.93 / 1.93 / 100 / 1.93
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; zoning; disinfection; ante and post-mortem inspections; no treatment of affected animals
Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s)
Administrative division / Species / Total vaccinated / Details
Atyrau / Sheep / 13 226 / [not provided]
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: National Veterinary Reference Center (National laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Sheep / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 25 Jun 2019 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The previous outbreak was also located in western Kazakhstan. In April 2019, one outbreak was reported in Mangystau Region. The event was resolved on 14 Jun 2019; see event summary and updated map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=30374.

Mangystau borders with Atyrau region, where current outbreak is located. See maps of Kazakhstan at https://tinyurl.com/yypxunkm and https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/kazakhstan-political-map.htm. - Mod.CRD


HealthMap/ProMED map available at:
Atyrau, Atyrau, Kazakhstan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6583678,46186]
